#: ../../guiding-participants/README.md:7
msgid "Guiding Participants"
msgstr ""

#: ../../guiding-participants/README.md:9
msgid ""
"\"Participation\" in an open source project is an interesting—and "
"somewhat amorphous—concept to describe. The line separating \"I'm just a "
"user! Don't talk to me about anything more\" and \"How can I help "
"contribute to this project?\" seem clear enough. Yet active participation"
" in a project begins the moment someone cares enough about the software "
"to do more than simply consume it. And because open source software is by"
" nature inclusive and participatory, most *users* become *participants* "
"rather quickly and easily—often by simply leaving a comment on the "
"project's blog, filing an issue in the project's tracker, or engaging "
"with the project on social media. By using open source software, they've "
"*already* begun participating in the process of making the software "
"better."
msgstr ""

#: ../../guiding-participants/README.md:11
msgid "Here are some examples of various types of participation:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../guiding-participants/README.md:13
msgid ""
"Talking to a friend about how much you like the software or the goals of "
"the open source project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../guiding-participants/README.md:14
msgid ""
"Engaging in a hallway or booth-side discussion about the software at a "
"conference or event."
msgstr ""

#: ../../guiding-participants/README.md:15
msgid ""
"Asking, upvoting, and answering questions about the software on various "
"forums."
msgstr ""

#: ../../guiding-participants/README.md:16
msgid ""
"Putting a sticker on your laptop to advertize your support of the "
"software."
msgstr ""

#: ../../guiding-participants/README.md:17
msgid ""
"Giving constructive feedback to a contributor about the software or "
"project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../guiding-participants/README.md:18
msgid "Recommending and offering to help others adopt and use the software."
msgstr ""

#: ../../guiding-participants/README.md:20
msgid "This section contains chapters that:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../guiding-participants/README.md:22
msgid "Discuss the ideas and forces behind the motivation to participate."
msgstr ""

#: ../../guiding-participants/README.md:23
msgid "Present details on how active participants benefit the project."
msgstr ""

#: ../../guiding-participants/README.md:25
msgid "This section is useful for you if:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../guiding-participants/README.md:27
msgid ""
"You are looking to understand the differences among communities made up "
"of less engaged users, enthusiastic participants, and active "
"contributors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../guiding-participants/README.md:28
msgid ""
"You want to understand what attracts people to participate in a pathway "
"toward contribution."
msgstr ""

#: ../../guiding-participants/README.md:29
msgid "You are looking to give your participation community a better experience."
msgstr ""

#: ../../guiding-participants/README.md:30
msgid "You wish to build bridges to enable participants to become contributors."
msgstr ""

#: ../../guiding-participants/README.md:31
msgid "You want to explore the benefit of user feedback in open source software."
msgstr ""

#: ../../guiding-participants/README.md:32
msgid ""
"You have reached the middle of this guidebook by starting at the "
"beginning, and are working your way toward the end."
msgstr ""
